Definition=void WinGetCursor (WINDOW *w, short *x, short *y);

[ROM Call]
Index=$14

[Description]
Returns the cursor location for a window.

[Explanation]
WinGetCursor returns the cursor location for the window pointed to by <I>w</I>
into <I>x</I> and <I>y</I>. But, I am not quite sure what the "cursor" is.
See notes about <A HREF="$$LINK(WinMoveCursor)">WinMoveCursor</A>.

